5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to the Gulf of Mexico; to rename the Gulf of
10 Mexico as the "Gulf of America"; and to require all state and
11 local entities and all employees of those entities to observe
12 and implement the name change, where practicable.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. (a) This act shall be known and may be cited
15 as the Gulf of America Act.
16 (b) For all purposes within the State of Alabama, the
17 body of water that borders the coast of Alabama, previously
18 known as the Gulf of Mexico, shall be known as the "Gulf of
19 America." Any reference to the Gulf of Mexico shall be deemed
20 to be a reference to the Gulf of America.
21 Section 2. Beginning October 1, 2026, all state and
22 local entities and their employees shall be required to do all
23 of the following:
24 (1) Refer to the body of water that borders the coast
25 of Alabama as the "Gulf of America."
26 (2) Reflect the "Gulf of America" terminology in all
27 newly created maps, documents, educational materials,
28 websites, official communications, and other resources.
Page 1

websites, official communications, and other resources.
HB2 Engrossed
29 (3)a. Make reasonable efforts to update all
30 pre-existing resources owned by state and local entities,
31 including, but not limited to, official state maps, documents,
32 educational materials, websites, and communications under
33 their jurisdiction to reflect the name change, where
34 practicable.
35 b. The requirements of paragraph a. shall not apply if
36 compliance would impose an operational or financial burden on
37 the state or local entity and their employees.
38 Section 3. Nothing in this section shall prohibit a
39 public K-12 school or public institution of higher education
40 from using the term "Gulf of Mexico" within a larger course of
41 academic instruction when reasonable for historical purposes.
42 Section 4. This act shall become effective on October
43 1, 2026.
